claim.claim-text:
1. A method for bidirectional data transmission of a data set between a data transmission device (1) and a data reception device (7) via at least one packet-oriented network device (3), in which connection-oriented switching is done, having the following steps: 
allocation of a data encapsulation protocol (10) to the data set to be transmitted connection-oriented in the data transmission device (1) or an external data terminal device (6) that is connected to the data transmission device (1), for an encapsulation of the data set to enable a connection-oriented data transmission of the data set; 
connection-oriented transmission of the encapsulated data set by means of at least one telecommunications device (4) from the data transmission device (1) to the packet-oriented network device (3); 
evaluation of the data encapsulation protocol (10) in the packet-oriented network device (3) for an unpacking of the data set to enable a packet-oriented data transmission of the data set; and 
packet-oriented transmission of the data set from the packet-oriented network device (3) to the data reception device (7).
